Exceptio Handling
------------------------
Exception is an abnormal condition.
In Java, exception is an event that disrupts the normal flow of the program

Types of Exception
--------------
1)  Checked -> Exception checked/idetified by the compiler

Example
InterruptedExcepion
IOException
FileNotFoundException etc.

2) Un-checked -> Exception which are not checked/idenified by compiler
Examples:
ArithmeticException
NullPointerException
NumberFormatException
ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException

String a ="abc";
int x=Integer.parseInt(a);

Handling Exceptions
----------------
try
{
statements
}
catch(Arithmetic Exception Type)
{
statements;
}
catch(NulPointerException Type)
{
statements
}
catch (NumberFormatException Type)
{
statements
}

one try block can have multiple catch block

Note------
Try..Catch can be use with :
                               Un-Checked      Checked   MethodLevel   Within the method
    Try..Catch                    Y              Y           N            Y
    throws                        N              Y           Y            N
